Arduino LCD Calculator
Arduino
C++
Hardware
LCD Keypad Shield
16×2 LCD
A hardware-based arithmetic calculator built for Arduino using the LCD Keypad Shield. Numbers and operators are selected via the shield's onboard buttons, with all input and results displayed live on the integrated 16×2 LCD — no Serial Monitor required.

Features

✓
Addition, subtraction, multiplication, division
✓
Full output on 16×2 LCD display
✓
Button-driven input (Up/Down/Left/Right/Select)
✓
Division-by-zero error handling
✓
Chained calculations
✓
No external wiring — shield plug-and-play
Hardware requirements

→ Arduino Uno (or compatible board)
→ LCD Keypad Shield (DFRobot-compatible, 16×2 LCD + 5 buttons)
→ Library: LiquidCrystal.h (built into Arduino IDE)
Shield pin mapping

LCD pins

RS → D8
EN → D9
D4–D7 → D4–D7
Button input

Analog A0
(resistor ladder)
Button controls

UP
Increment digit / cycle operator
DOWN
Decrement digit / cycle operator
RIGHT
Confirm entry / advance to next step
SELECT
Calculate result (=)
LEFT
Clear / reset
Getting started

1
Plug the LCD Keypad Shield onto your Arduino Uno

2
Open calculator.ino in the Arduino IDE

3
Select your board and COM port, then upload

4
Use the onboard buttons to enter numbers, select an operator, and press SELECT to calculate

LCD display layout

42 + 58        
= 100         
Row 1: current expression  ·  Row 2: result
